  • Method Details

    • setLevel

      void setLevel​(LogLevel level)
      Sets the log level to log at for the logger. If a log operation is invoked at a finer resolution then the set level, it is ignored. For example

      setLevel(LogLevel.FINE);
      finer("I will not get logged");
      fine("I will get logged");
      severe("I will get logged");
      Parameters:
      level - the new log level to log at
      See Also:
      LogLevel

    • setTarget

      void setTarget​(java.lang.String path) throws java.io.IOException
      Sets an external target file. The external target is guaranteed to receive all logs after this method returns except for the few cases listed below.
      • The target exists but is a directory rather than a regular file
      • The target does not exist but cannot be created
      • The target cannot be opened for any other reason
      In the cases listed above, an IOException will be thrown.
      Parameters:
      path - the new target
      Throws:
      java.io.IOException - if the named file exists but is a directory rather than a regular file, does not exist but cannot be created, or cannot be opened for any other reason
